Message:
Sure, I can help you with that! To integrate a Postback pixel with ClickBank on NewsBreak, follow these steps:
1. Log in to your ClickBank account and click 'Accounts' on the left panel. Select your desired account name.
2. Within your account page, click on 'Vendor Settings' on the top navigation bar.
3. In the 'Vendor Settings' view, click 'My Site' near the top of the screen.
4. Once you access the site configuration view, scroll down until you see the 'Advanced Tool' section. Click on 'Edit' on the right side of this section.
5. Name your event, choose 'Postback' as your event tracking type, select 'ClickBank' as your 3rd party tracking service, and choose 'sale' as your conversion event in the dropdown.
6. Test the Postback integration by entering the URL you get from ClickBank (offer URL or test URL) and clicking 'Go test'.
7. Make sure to use the parameter "tid" in your URL to pass through the click ID: tid=__CALLBACK_PARAM__
For more detailed instructions, you can refer to this article: [How to set up a ClickBank Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/23746617571341-How-to-set-up-a-ClickBank-Postback-on-NewsBreak).

Great question! While Google Ads Keyword Planner is a tool specifically for Google Ads, you can still use it to get an idea of the CPC and search volume for keywords in your niche. Hereâ€™s how you can use it to inform your NewsBreak ad campaigns:
1. **Access Google Ads Keyword Planner:** Log in to your Google Ads account and navigate to the Keyword Planner tool.
2. **Find Keywords:** Enter keywords related to the survival niche into the Keyword Planner. It will provide you with data on search volume, competition, and estimated CPC for those keywords.
3. **Analyze Data:** Use this data to understand which keywords are popular and have a reasonable CPC. This information can help you choose effective keywords for your NewsBreak ads.
4. **Apply Insights:** When setting up your NewsBreak ad campaign, use the insights from the Keyword Planner to target similar keywords and optimize your ad copy and targeting settings.
